body.name: Genuine Joe 99737 Launder-X Laundry Powder Detergent, No. 40, Ast
body.description: Laundry powder detergent penetrates deep down into fabric fibers, removing ground-in dirt and stains. With the added cleaning power of borax, this nontoxic detergent leaves your white's whiter and your colors brighter. It also acts as a water conditioner to control alkalinity and deodorizes clothing naturally. Detergent dissolves completely and rinses away completely, leaving no residue in your clothes. It is safe and effective at all temperatures and for all washables.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 30, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars This stuff is great
reviews.reviewText: I love the economicalness of using this detergent. Instead of spending $20 on laundry soap every 2 to 3 weeks (we do a lot of laundry), I buy one of these buckets and it lasts right around 9 months. I use around a quarter cup a load give or take, depending on what I'm washing. I like the way it cleans and that it doesn't have much of a scent. And we haven't had any issues with skin problems or irritations. I am careful about breathing it in when moving between buckets and containers. Also who doesn't love having a three gallon bucket to use when you finish with the soap. It's the perfect size. Only warning, it is heavy, I would not want to be responsible for hauling it up multiple flights of stairs.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 28, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Wow, as good as tide but orderless...
reviews.reviewText: Great cleaning soap at a definite budget price. Tide works no better but I do wish it had a good fresh scent like tide and other soaps that do not work as good as this soap for sure. Tide and this soap are definitely equal as I'm in badly stained clothing from vehicles, welding daily and WOW is my one word review for a great five star value that I'd buy anyway over tide unless same price and tide would only win for it's scent then. But to save so much and considered to other cheap soaps even this soap is surely great as it cleans heavily soiled clothes like the best money can buy for sure, and I've try'd all the stain and spot removers before and this with a brush and some scrubbing works great and I think the powder form is actually a better cleaner for such things being somewhat abrasive and working itself between the clothing and substance staining them, think of it as comet vs soft liquid scubber. Hands down comment wins every time. Great product that I will be buying from now on at the best of prices for twice the soap of all but one I mentioned already... What a bargain... Says commercial grade and I thought just a selling ploy or gimmick word, but after around 20 loads so far I'm a believer of that term commercial quality now for sure and finally a soap that is what it claims to be unlikeless budget brands like All, Snuggle, Arm & Hammer, and many others I've tried over the years... If your value for dollar shopping you won't be at this soap at any price for sure... Love it... Thanks 👍👍

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 4, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I was skeptical of this product. The facts of Life can be found in our clichés, and "If it seems to good to be true, it is" came to mind.Lower price with as good as results, seems to be too good to be true.I received so much more for what the same cost I would have for a large box of the top brands, so I expected to have to use more. I decided to do a test load first to have point of reference.This product does not suds up, but it cleans just fine.I have now run dozens of loads of every kind and can attest to it's quality.No suds, no added wonderful fresh lilac aroma, but it cleans as well as others.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 12, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Purchased because of 40 lb continer pail size.
reviews.reviewText: I usually get detergent in 40lb pails, The normal brand i buy changed to a smaller 36 lb pail.I use the pails when detergent is gone and the 36 lb pail is not usable for my application.So GI Joe gets my purchases due to pail size and lid construction.Some people (Such as me) use the pails for other applications after detergent is gone.Also the GI Joe detergent works well and cleans very dirty work clothing with no issues.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 25, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Very heavy. However with a family of 7 it's worth the money! Much better option than small bottles. This lasts over 6 months in my house!The quality is great! Removes stains, no residue left behind. It's a white powder and the smell is neutral.

reviews.reviewTitle: A little goes a long way
reviews.reviewText: Just lightly scented and works really well. I wanted to switch to powder because I was told it's better for front loading machines and that 1-2 tbsps is enough. I put 1 tbsp in the soap dispenser area and it's doing a great job getting our clothes clean and fresh. And it's also going to last forever so it's a great deal. We do have softened water so less soap works well but if you have hard water you may need to use a little more but this bucket will still last a long long time!

I laughed out loud when I picked this up from the carrier. It was so much bigger than I was expecting and very heavy. Glad my husband was there carry it inside for me😂I mix in borax, washing soda, baking soda, and a little TSP and my laundry comes out clean and fresh every time! Once this runs out (which won't be for a long time!) I will definitely order again as it was a good price for the amount.

reviews.reviewTitle: Back to clean laundry the old fashioned way
reviews.reviewText: I threw out those costly liquid detergents . Our household has several loads of laundry each week. We have been using this for several weeks and I am very pleased. Joe laundry powder does the job and more. I no longer use bleach or spot treat stains. For stains just add a little extra powder to the load and it will do its thing. For ceramic floors add a little to the bucket and get the floors clean. I also use it on my granite counter top. Gets the counters clean with a great shine to boot. Love love this product and love the savings.

I really like the smell of this powder laundry detergent! It's a orange scent which I love! I feel this is well worth the money and in a container I can use after the soap is gone. Thanks for making a great laundry soap.
Great product for the price, alot of soap for a reasonable price. Works great on clothes, you dont need so much soap in each load of laundry.
